<paragraph id="335F36A86065FFC0FF62FE8CC86AF316" blockId="6.[136,1452,158,581]" pageId="6" pageNumber="124">
<emphasis id="0194EABA6065FFC0FF62FE8CCC6DF076" bold="true" box="[189,294,266,292]" pageId="6" pageNumber="124">Notes:—</emphasis>
The phylogenetic result (
<figureCitation id="ABDB2A2D6065FFC0FD9BFE8CCF8CF076" box="[580,711,266,292]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[136,229,1768,1790]" captionTargetBox="[207,1392,580,1728]" captionTargetId="figure-168@2.[190,1398,569,1744]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Phylogenetic tree generated from maximum likelihood (ML) analysis based on combined LSU, ITS and SSU sequence data. ML bootstrap support values greater than 75% and Bayesian posterior probabilities (PP) greater than 0.95 are given above the nodes, branches with 100% ML BP and 1.0 PP are in thickened.Taxa representing by type speciments (or ex-type strains) are highlighted in bold. Newly generated sequences are indicated in red.The tree is rooted with Amniculicola immersa (CBS 123083) and A. parva (CBS 123092). The figures on the right side show the morphology of the type species in each genus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5314290" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5314290/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="124">FIGURE. 1</figureCitation>
) showed that the new taxa (
<taxonomicName id="F4E04D2B6065FFC0FBCDFE8CC803F076" box="[1042,1352,266,292]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Tetraplosphaeriaceae" genus="Aquatisphaeria" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="6" pageNumber="124" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="thailandica">
<emphasis id="0194EABA6065FFC0FBCDFE8CC803F076" box="[1042,1352,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="124">Aquatisphaeria thailandica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) formed a distinct clade within 
<taxonomicName id="F4E04D2B6065FFC0FE77FEA8CFD0F01A" box="[424,667,302,328]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Tetraplosphaeriaceae" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="6" pageNumber="124" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="family">
<emphasis id="0194EABA6065FFC0FE77FEA8CFD0F01A" box="[424,667,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="124">Tetraplosphaeriaceae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It is phylogenetically close to 
<taxonomicName id="F4E04D2B6065FFC0FBF0FEA8C98AF01A" box="[1071,1217,302,328]" genus="Ernakulamia" kingdom="Fungi" pageId="6" pageNumber="124" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0194EABA6065FFC0FBF0FEA8C98AF01A" box="[1071,1217,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="124">Ernakulamia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="F4E04D2B6065FFC0FAD6FEA8C8EEF01A" box="[1289,1445,302,328]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Tetraplosphaeriaceae" genus="Shrungabeeja" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="6" pageNumber="124" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0194EABA6065FFC0FAD6FEA8C8EEF01A" box="[1289,1445,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="124">Shrungabeeja</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="F4E04D2B6065FFC0FF57FED4CC7EF03E" authorityName="W. L. Li, N. G. Liu &amp; Jian K. Liu" authorityYear="2021" box="[136,309,338,364]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Tetraplosphaeriaceae" genus="Aquatisphaeria" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="6" pageNumber="124" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0194EABA6065FFC0FF57FED4CC7EF03E" box="[136,309,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="124">Aquatisphaeria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to the other genera in 
<taxonomicName id="F4E04D2B6065FFC0FD60FED4CEF9F03E" box="[703,946,338,364]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Tetraplosphaeriaceae" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="6" pageNumber="124" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="family">
<emphasis id="0194EABA6065FFC0FD60FED4CEF9F03E" box="[703,946,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="124">Tetraplosphaeriaceae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having monoblastic conidiogenous cells and solitary, subglobose or turbinate conidia with filiform or horn-like appendages. The genera 
<taxonomicName id="F4E04D2B6065FFC0FB34FEF0C8EFF0C2" box="[1259,1444,374,400]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Tetraplosphaeriaceae" genus="Pseudotetraploa" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="6" pageNumber="124" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0194EABA6065FFC0FB34FEF0C8EFF0C2" box="[1259,1444,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="124">Pseudotetraploa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="F4E04D2B6065FFC0FF57FE1CCC5CF0E6" box="[136,279,410,436]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Tetraplosphaeriaceae" genus="Quadricrura" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="6" pageNumber="124" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0194EABA6065FFC0FF57FE1CCC5CF0E6" box="[136,279,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="124">Quadricrura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="F4E04D2B6065FFC0FEF4FE1CCCDCF0E6" authorityName="M.J.Berkeley &amp; Broome" authorityYear="1850" box="[299,407,410,436]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Tetraplosphaeriaceae" genus="Tetraploa" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="6" pageNumber="124" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0194EABA6065FFC0FEF4FE1CCCDCF0E6" box="[299,407,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="124">Tetraploa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="F4E04D2B6065FFC0FE00FE1CCFCEF0E6" box="[479,645,410,436]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Tetraplosphaeriaceae" genus="Triplosphaeria" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="6" pageNumber="124" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0194EABA6065FFC0FE00FE1CCFCEF0E6" box="[479,645,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="124">Triplosphaeria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be easily distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="F4E04D2B6065FFC0FBC0FE1CC987F0E6" authorityName="W. L. Li, N. G. Liu &amp; Jian K. Liu" authorityYear="2021" box="[1055,1228,410,436]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Tetraplosphaeriaceae" genus="Aquatisphaeria" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="6" pageNumber="124" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0194EABA6065FFC0FBC0FE1CC987F0E6" box="[1055,1228,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="124">Aquatisphaeria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the absence of conidiophores (
<bibRefCitation id="57714B596065FFC0FEEAFE38CF40F08A" author="Tanaka, K. &amp; Hirayama, K. &amp; Yonezawa, H. &amp; Hatakeyama, S. &amp; Harada, Y. &amp; Sano, T. &amp; Shirouzu, T. &amp; Hosoya, T." box="[309,523,446,473]" pageId="6" pageNumber="124" pagination="175 - 209" refId="ref10605" refString="Tanaka, K., Hirayama, K., Yonezawa, H., Hatakeyama, S., Harada, Y., Sano, T., Shirouzu, T. &amp; Hosoya, T. (2009) Molecular taxonomy of bambusicolous fungi: Tetraplosphaeriaceae, a new pleosporalean family with Tetraploa - like anamorphs. Studies in Mycology 64: 175 - 209. https: // doi. org / 10.3114 / sim. 2009.64.10" type="journal article" year="2009">
Tanaka 
<emphasis id="0194EABA6065FFC0FE50FE39CC8BF08A" box="[399,448,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="124">et al</emphasis>
. 2009
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="F4E04D2B6065FFC0FDC2FE38CFE4F08A" box="[541,687,446,472]" genus="Ernakulamia" kingdom="Fungi" pageId="6" pageNumber="124" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0194EABA6065FFC0FDC2FE38CFE4F08A" box="[541,687,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="124">Ernakulamia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has monotretic conidiogenous cells which differs from other genera of 
<taxonomicName id="F4E04D2B6065FFC0FF78FE64CCD1F0AE" box="[167,410,482,508]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Tetraplosphaeriaceae" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="6" pageNumber="124" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="family">
<emphasis id="0194EABA6065FFC0FF78FE64CCD1F0AE" box="[167,410,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="124">Tetraplosphaeriaceae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
including 
<taxonomicName id="F4E04D2B6065FFC0FDCCFE64CEF7F0AE" authority="(Delgado et al. 2017)" baseAuthorityName="Delgado" baseAuthorityYear="2017" box="[531,956,482,509]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Tetraplosphaeriaceae" genus="Aquatisphaeria" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="6" pageNumber="124" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0194EABA6065FFC0FDCCFE64CF8BF0AE" box="[531,704,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="124">Aquatisphaeria</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="57714B596065FFC0FD10FE64CEFFF0AE" author="Delgado, G. &amp; Koukol, O. &amp; Caceres, O. &amp; Piepenbring, M." box="[719,948,482,509]" pageId="6" pageNumber="124" pagination="435 - 451" refId="ref5486" refString="Delgado, G., Koukol, O., Caceres, O. &amp; Piepenbring, M. (2017) The Phylogenetic Placement of Ernakulamia cochinensis within Pleosporales (Dothideomycetes, Ascomycota). Cryptogamie, Mycologie 38 (4): 435 - 451. https: // doi. org / 10.7872 / crym / v 38. iss 4.2017.435" type="journal article" year="2017">
Delgado 
<emphasis id="0194EABA6065FFC0FCE8FE65CE22F0AE" box="[823,873,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="124">et al</emphasis>
. 2017
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="F4E04D2B6065FFC0FC18FE64C93FF0AE" box="[967,1140,482,508]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Tetraplosphaeriaceae" genus="Aquatisphaeria" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="6" pageNumber="124" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0194EABA6065FFC0FC18FE64C93FF0AE" box="[967,1140,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="124">Aquatisphaeria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName id="F4E04D2B6065FFC0FB2DFE64C8C5F0AE" box="[1266,1422,482,508]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Tetraplosphaeriaceae" genus="Shrungabeeja" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="6" pageNumber="124" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0194EABA6065FFC0FB2DFE64C8C5F0AE" box="[1266,1422,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="124">Shrungabeeja</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having monoblastic conidiogenous cells and macronematous conidiophores. However, conidiophores in 
<taxonomicName id="F4E04D2B6065FFC0FACFFD80C8E7F372" box="[1296,1452,518,544]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Tetraplosphaeriaceae" genus="Shrungabeeja" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="6" pageNumber="124" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0194EABA6065FFC0FACFFD80C8E7F372" box="[1296,1452,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="124">Shrungabeeja</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are conspicuously longer than 
<taxonomicName id="F4E04D2B6065FFC0FE01FDACCFC0F316" box="[478,651,554,580]" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Tetraplosphaeriaceae" genus="Aquatisphaeria" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pleosporales" pageId="6" pageNumber="124" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0194EABA6065FFC0FE01FDACCFC0F316" box="[478,651,554,580]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="124">Aquatisphaeria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of three to six times (Zhang 
<emphasis id="0194EABA6065FFC0FC10FDADC94BF316" box="[975,1024,554,580]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="124">et al</emphasis>
. 2017, 
<bibRefCitation id="57714B596065FFC0FB8BFDADC85EF316" author="Dong, W. &amp; Wang, B. &amp; Hyde, K. D. &amp; McKenzie, E. H. C. &amp; Raja, H. A. &amp; Tanaka, K. &amp; Abdel-Wahab, M. A. &amp; Abdel-Aziz, F. A. &amp; Doilom, M. &amp; Phookamsak, R. &amp; Hongsanan, S. &amp; Wanasinghe, D. N. &amp; Yu, X. D. &amp; Wang, G. N. &amp; Yang, H. &amp; Yang, J. &amp; Thambugala, K. M. &amp; Tian, Q. &amp; Luo, Z. L. &amp; Yang, J. B. &amp; Miller, A. N. &amp; Fournier, J. &amp; Boonmee, S. &amp; Hu, D. M. &amp; Nalumpang, S. &amp; Zhang, H." box="[1108,1301,554,581]" pageId="6" pageNumber="124" pagination="319 - 575" refId="ref5725" refString="Dong, W., Wang, B., Hyde, K. D., McKenzie, E. H. C., Raja, H. A., Tanaka, K., Abdel-Wahab, M. A., Abdel-Aziz, F. A., Doilom, M., Phookamsak, R., Hongsanan, S., Wanasinghe, D. N., Yu, X. D., Wang, G. N., Yang, H., Yang, J., Thambugala, K. M., Tian, Q., Luo, Z. L., Yang, J. B., Miller, A. N., Fournier, J., Boonmee, S., Hu, D. M., Nalumpang, S. &amp; Zhang, H. (2020) Freshwater Dothideomycetes. Fungal Diversity 105: 319 - 575. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 13225 - 020 - 00463 - 5" type="journal article" year="2020">
Dong 
<emphasis id="0194EABA6065FFC0FB46FDADC980F316" box="[1177,1227,554,580]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="124">et al</emphasis>
. 2020
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
